 of Breaking Through" and "A Spiritual Morphology of Poetry;" several shorter pieces on topics including collecting invertebrates and the impact of modernization on Mexican village life; and more. An engaging critical biography and a number of rare photographs offer a new and richly detailed view of Ricketts’s life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMarine invertebrateszMexicozCalifornia, Gulf of. 0aMarine invertebrateszPacific Coast (U.S.) 0aMarine invertebrateszPacific Coast (U.S.). 0aTeleology. 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh  aa spiritual morphology of poetry.  abiography.  acalifornia.  acannery row.  aconservation.  aearth sciences.  aecology.  aedward ricketts.  aenvironment.  aenvironmentalism.  agulf of california.  ainvertebrates.  alog from the sea of cortez.  amarine biology.  amexican village.  amexico.  amonterey.  anatural history.  anatural world.  anaturalism.  anaturalist.  anature.  anonfiction.  aoceanography.  ascience.  asteinbeck.  athe philosophy of breaking through.  atravel writing.  atravel.  atravelogue.  avillage.  awildlife.1 aRicketts, Edward F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRodger, Katharine A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093266140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520932661423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520932661/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles